Preconditions:
The value of 'n' should be a positive integer representing the number of cities.
The 'edges' array should be a 2D array representing the connections between cities.
The 'price' array should be a 1D array representing the cost of traveling between cities.
The 'trips' array should be a 2D array representing the trips to be performed.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the minimum total price sum to perform all the given trips.